{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":680,"text":"I must have been about 12 years old"},{"time":3120,"text":"when my dad took me\nto an exhibition on space,"},{"time":7200,"text":"not far from here, in Brussels."},{"time":9840,"text":"And the year was about --\nI think it was 1988,"},{"time":12680,"text":"so it was the end of the Cold War."},{"time":15280,"text":"There was a bit of an upmanship going on\nbetween the Americans and the Russians"},{"time":19040,"text":"bringing bits to that exhibition."},{"time":22240,"text":"NASA brought a big blow-up space shuttle,"},{"time":25800,"text":"but the Russians,\nthey brought a Mir space station."},{"time":30760,"text":"It was actually the training module,"},{"time":32840,"text":"and you could go inside\nand check it all out."},{"time":35360,"text":"It was the real thing --"},{"time":36960,"text":"where the buttons were,\nwhere the wires were,"},{"time":39120,"text":"where the astronauts were eating,\nwhere they were working."},{"time":42240,"text":"And when I came home,"},{"time":44160,"text":"the first thing I did,\nI started drawing spaceships."},{"time":48320,"text":"Now, these weren't\nscience fiction spaceships, no."},{"time":52400,"text":"They were actually technical drawings."},{"time":54320,"text":"They were cutaway sections"},{"time":57000,"text":"of what kind of structure\nwould be made out of,"},{"time":59960,"text":"where the wires were,\nwhere the screws were."}]},{"cues":[{"time":63600,"text":"So fortunately, I didn't\nbecome a space engineer,"},{"time":66720,"text":"but I did become an architect."},{"time":69920,"text":"These are some of the projects\nthat I've been involved with"},{"time":72720,"text":"over the last decade and a half."},{"time":75000,"text":"All these projects are quite different,\nquite different shapes,"},{"time":78480,"text":"and it is because they are built\nfor different environments."},{"time":81360,"text":"They have different constraints."},{"time":84040,"text":"And I think design\nbecomes really interesting"},{"time":87480,"text":"when you get really harsh constraints."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92160,"text":"Now, these projects\nhave been all over the world."},{"time":96320,"text":"A few years ago,\nthis map wasn't good enough."},{"time":99640,"text":"It was too small."},{"time":101080,"text":"We had to add this one,"},{"time":103600,"text":"because we were going to do\na project on the Moon"},{"time":107160,"text":"for the European Space Agency;"},{"time":108920,"text":"they asked us to design a Moon habitat --"},{"time":111440,"text":"and one on Mars with NASA,"},{"time":114600,"text":"a competition to look\nat a habitation on Mars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120280,"text":"Whenever you go to another place,"},{"time":123960,"text":"as an architect"},{"time":125440,"text":"and try to design something,"},{"time":128360,"text":"you look at the local architecture,\nthe precedents that are there."},{"time":131840,"text":"Now, on the Moon,\nit's kind of difficult, of course,"},{"time":134320,"text":"because there's only this."},{"time":135600,"text":"There's only the Apollo missions."},{"time":139400,"text":"So last that we went there,\nI wasn't even born yet,"},{"time":142560,"text":"and we only spent about three days there."},{"time":146680,"text":"So for me, that's kind of\na long camping trip, isn't it,"},{"time":150960,"text":"but a rather expensive one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":154480,"text":"Now, the tricky thing,"},{"time":156800,"text":"when you're going to build\non another planet or a moon,"},{"time":160760,"text":"is how to get it there,\nhow to get it there."},{"time":164320,"text":"So first of all,"},{"time":167360,"text":"to get a kilogram, for example,\nto the Moon's surface,"},{"time":170600,"text":"it will cost about 200,000 dollars,"},{"time":174840,"text":"very expensive."},{"time":176240,"text":"So you want to keep it very light."},{"time":179440,"text":"Second, space. Space is limited. Right?"},{"time":182440,"text":"This is the Ariane 5 rocket."},{"time":184480,"text":"The space you have there"},{"time":185760,"text":"is about four and a half meters\nby seven meters, not that much."},{"time":191000,"text":"So it needs to be an architectural system"},{"time":194160,"text":"that is both compact,\nor compactable, and light,"},{"time":198440,"text":"and I think I've got one right here."},{"time":202320,"text":"It's very compact,"},{"time":204480,"text":"and it's very light."},{"time":207080,"text":"And actually,"},{"time":208760,"text":"this is one I made earlier."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213440,"text":"Now, there's one problem with it,"},{"time":216960,"text":"that inflatables"},{"time":220520,"text":"are quite fragile."},{"time":223360,"text":"They need to be protected,"},{"time":226840,"text":"specifically, when you go\nto a very harsh environment like the Moon."},{"time":233600,"text":"Look at it like this."},{"time":237080,"text":"The temperature difference on a Moon base"},{"time":239360,"text":"could be anything up to 200 degrees."},{"time":241440,"text":"On one side of the base,\nit could be 100 degrees Celsius"},{"time":245360,"text":"and on the other side,\nit could be minus 100 degrees."},{"time":248400,"text":"We need to protect ourselves from that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251720,"text":"The Moon also does not have\nany magnetic fields,"},{"time":257120,"text":"which means that any radiation --\nsolar radiation, cosmic radiation --"},{"time":262120,"text":"will hit the surface."},{"time":264320,"text":"We need to protect ourselves\nfrom that as well,"},{"time":266560,"text":"protect the astronauts from that."},{"time":269040,"text":"And then third,"},{"time":270640,"text":"but definitely not last,"},{"time":272440,"text":"the Moon does not have any atmosphere,"},{"time":276120,"text":"which means any meteorites coming into it\nwill not get burned up,"},{"time":280920,"text":"and they'll hit the surface."},{"time":282320,"text":"That's why the Moon is full of craters."},{"time":285560,"text":"Again, we need to protect\nthe astronauts from that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289160,"text":"So what kind of structure do we need?"},{"time":291000,"text":"Well, the best thing is really a cave,"},{"time":295840,"text":"because a cave has a lot of mass,\nand we need mass."},{"time":298280,"text":"We need mass to protect\nourselves from the temperatures,"},{"time":301280,"text":"from the radiation"},{"time":302920,"text":"and from the meteorites."},{"time":305080,"text":"So this is how we solved it."},{"time":308000,"text":"We have indeed the blue part,\nas you can see."},{"time":311040,"text":"That's an inflatable for our Moon base."},{"time":313800,"text":"It gives a lot of living space\nand a lot of lab space,"},{"time":317960,"text":"and attached to it you have a cylinder,"},{"time":320800,"text":"and that has all\nthe support structures in,"},{"time":323880,"text":"all the life support and also the airlock."},{"time":328080,"text":"And on top of that, we have a structure,\nthat domed structure,"},{"time":332400,"text":"that protects ourselves,"},{"time":333800,"text":"has a lot of mass in it."},{"time":336440,"text":"Where are we going\nto get this material from?"},{"time":338600,"text":"Are we going to bring concrete and cement\nfrom Earth to the Moon?"},{"time":341720,"text":"Well, of course not,\nbecause it's way too heavy."},{"time":344280,"text":"It's too expensive."},{"time":345560,"text":"So we're going to go\nand use local materials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349440,"text":"Now, local materials are something\nwe deal with on Earth as well."},{"time":352560,"text":"Wherever we build\nor whatever country we build in,"},{"time":354960,"text":"we always look at,\nwhat are the local materials here?"},{"time":357480,"text":"The problem with the Moon is,\nwhat are the local materials?"},{"time":360360,"text":"Well, there's not that many."},{"time":362600,"text":"Actually, we have one."},{"time":364200,"text":"It's moondust,"},{"time":366480,"text":"or, fancier scientific name,\nregolith, Moon regolith."},{"time":373080,"text":"Great thing is, it's everywhere, right?"},{"time":375400,"text":"The surface is covered with it."},{"time":377440,"text":"It's about 20 centimeters\nup to a few meters everywhere."},{"time":382040,"text":"But how are we going to build with it?"},{"time":384760,"text":"Well, we're going to use a 3D printer."},{"time":388560,"text":"Whenever I ask any of you\nwhat a 3D printer is,"},{"time":390800,"text":"you're probably all thinking, well,\nprobably something about this size"},{"time":394160,"text":"and it would print things\nthat are about this size."},{"time":398800,"text":"So of course I'm not going to bring\na massive 3D printer to the Moon"},{"time":402040,"text":"to print my Moon base."},{"time":403320,"text":"I'm going to use a much smaller device,\nsomething like this one here."},{"time":408640,"text":"So this is a small device,\na small robot rover,"},{"time":411880,"text":"that has a little scoop,"},{"time":414080,"text":"and it brings the regolith to the dome"},{"time":417840,"text":"and then it lays down\na thin layer of regolith,"},{"time":422000,"text":"and then you would have\nthe robot that will solidify it,"},{"time":425440,"text":"layer by layer,"},{"time":427480,"text":"until it creates, after a few months,"},{"time":430440,"text":"the full base."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433600,"text":"You might have noticed"},{"time":435200,"text":"that it's quite a particular\nstructure that we're printing,"},{"time":439440,"text":"and I've got a little example here."},{"time":443280,"text":"What we call this\nis a closed-cell foam structure."},{"time":448640,"text":"Looks quite natural."},{"time":450840,"text":"The reason why we're using this"},{"time":452520,"text":"as part of that shell structure"},{"time":454600,"text":"is that we only need\nto solidify certain parts,"},{"time":459120,"text":"which means we have to bring\nless binder from Earth,"},{"time":462400,"text":"and it becomes much lighter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464840,"text":"Now --"},{"time":467640,"text":"that approach of designing something"},{"time":470560,"text":"and then covering it\nwith a protective dome"},{"time":473520,"text":"we also did for our Mars project."},{"time":476760,"text":"You can see it here, three domes."},{"time":478800,"text":"And you see the printers\nprinting these dome structures."},{"time":483200,"text":"There's a big difference\nbetween Mars and the Moon,"},{"time":485640,"text":"and let me explain it."},{"time":487040,"text":"This diagram shows you to scale"},{"time":490560,"text":"the size of Earth and the Moon\nand the real distance,"},{"time":494280,"text":"about 400,000 kilometers."},{"time":496920,"text":"If we then go to Mars,"},{"time":499720,"text":"the distance from Mars to Earth --"},{"time":501400,"text":"and this picture here"},{"time":502640,"text":"is taken by the rover on Mars,\nCuriosity, looking back at Earth."},{"time":507680,"text":"You kind of see the little speckle there,\nthat's Earth, 400 million kilometers away."},{"time":513039,"text":"The problem with that distance"},{"time":514520,"text":"is that it's a thousand times the distance\nof the Earth to the Moon, pretty far away,"},{"time":518559,"text":"but there's no direct radio contact\nwith, for example, the Curiosity rover."},{"time":525080,"text":"So I cannot teleoperate it from Earth."},{"time":528960,"text":"I can't say, \"Oh, Mars rover, go left,\""},{"time":533200,"text":"because that signal\nwould take 20 minutes to get to Mars."},{"time":537360,"text":"Then the rover might go left,"},{"time":540000,"text":"and then it will take another 20 minutes\nbefore it can tell me,"},{"time":543000,"text":"\"Oh yeah, I went left.\""},{"time":544960,"text":"So the distance,"},{"time":546760,"text":"so rovers and robots"},{"time":550000,"text":"and going to have to work autonomously."},{"time":553120,"text":"The only issue with it"},{"time":555040,"text":"is that missions to Mars are highly risky."},{"time":559480,"text":"We've only seen it a few weeks ago."},{"time":562960,"text":"So what if half the mission\ndoesn't arrive at Mars."},{"time":566440,"text":"What do we do?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":567720,"text":"Well, instead of building\njust one or two rovers"},{"time":570840,"text":"like we did on the Moon,"},{"time":572240,"text":"we're going to build hundreds of them."},{"time":574880,"text":"And it's a bit like\na termite's mound, you know?"},{"time":578440,"text":"Termites, I would take half\nof the colony of the termites away,"},{"time":582000,"text":"they would still be able\nto build the mound."},{"time":584520,"text":"It might take a little bit longer."},{"time":586560,"text":"Same here."},{"time":587800,"text":"If half of our rovers\nor robots don't arrive,"},{"time":590840,"text":"well, it will take a bit longer,\nbut you will still be able to do it."},{"time":594160,"text":"So here we even have\nthree different rovers."},{"time":597240,"text":"In the back, you see the digger."},{"time":599520,"text":"It's really good at digging regolith."},{"time":602960,"text":"Then we have the transporter,"},{"time":606520,"text":"great at taking regolith\nand bringing it to the structure."},{"time":610360,"text":"And the last ones,\nthe little ones with the little legs,"},{"time":613000,"text":"they don't need to move a lot."},{"time":614480,"text":"What they do is they go\nand sit on a layer of regolith"},{"time":617440,"text":"and then microwave it together,"},{"time":619400,"text":"and layer by layer\ncreate that dome structure."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624160,"text":"Now --"},{"time":627440,"text":"we also want to try that out,"},{"time":628880,"text":"so we went out on a road trip,"},{"time":631240,"text":"and we created our own swarm of robots."},{"time":637640,"text":"There you go."},{"time":638920,"text":"So we built 10 of those.\nIt's a small swarm."},{"time":641480,"text":"And we took six tons of sand,"},{"time":644520,"text":"and we tried out how these little robots"},{"time":647920,"text":"would actually be able\nto move sand around,"},{"time":650280,"text":"Earth sand in this case."},{"time":652400,"text":"And they were not teleoperated. Right?"},{"time":655680,"text":"Nobody was telling them go left, go right,\nor giving them a predescribed path."},{"time":660080,"text":"No. They were given a task:"},{"time":662320,"text":"move sand from this area to that area."},{"time":666280,"text":"And if they came across\nan obstacle, like a rock,"},{"time":669120,"text":"they had to sort it out themselves."},{"time":671520,"text":"Or they came across another robot,"},{"time":673200,"text":"they had to be able to make decisions."},{"time":676080,"text":"Or even if half of them fell out,\ntheir batteries died,"},{"time":679200,"text":"they still had to be able\nto finish that task."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684120,"text":"Now, I've talked about redundancy."},{"time":688960,"text":"But that was not only with the robots."},{"time":690840,"text":"It was also with the habitats."},{"time":692320,"text":"On the Mars project,\nwe decided to do three domes,"},{"time":698280,"text":"because if one didn't arrive,"},{"time":701160,"text":"the other two could still form a base,"},{"time":703200,"text":"and that was mainly because\neach of the domes"},{"time":705360,"text":"actually have a life support system\nbuilt in the floor,"},{"time":709320,"text":"so they can work independently."}]},{"cues":[{"time":712040,"text":"So in a way, you might think,\nwell, this is pretty crazy."},{"time":717720,"text":"Why would you, as an architect,\nget involved in space?"},{"time":722240,"text":"Because it's such a technical field."},{"time":726400,"text":"Well, I'm actually really convinced"},{"time":729480,"text":"that from a creative view\nor a design view,"},{"time":734120,"text":"you are able to solve really hard\nand really constrained problems."},{"time":740200,"text":"And I really feel that there is\na place for design and architecture"},{"time":744040,"text":"in projects like\ninterplanetary habitation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":748320,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":749560,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}